{
  "texts": [
    "The worry is if humans in warfare begin to eschew responsibility, then the connective tissue of war as a political act begins to fray.",
    "Thus, responsibility must be retained.",
    "Miller (2020) argues that commanders must retain meaningful human control (MHC) of weapons if AI systems begin to select and engage targets autonomously, a task previously done by humans, in order to maintain commitments to IHL.",
    "He says, \"commanders will remain obligated to take necessary and reasonable measures to prevent and suppress violations of IHL by their forces.",
    "Therefore, MHC should be defined as the control necessary for commanders to satisfy this obligation\" (p. 545)."
  ]
}